				<article id="post-407" class="post-407 project type-project status-publish has-post-thumbnail hentry project_category-citythatworks et_pb_post">

				
					<div class="entry-content">
					<div id="et-boc" class="et-boc">
			
			<div class="et_builder_inner_content et_pb_gutters3">
				<div class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_0 et_pb_fullwidth_section et_section_regular">
				
				
				
				
					<section class="et_pb_module et_pb_fullwidth_header et_pb_fullwidth_header_0 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_text_align_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_fullwidth_header_container center">
					<div class="header-content-container center">
					<div class="header-content">
						
						<h1 class="et_pb_module_header">Making the City Work</h1>
						<span class="et_pb_fullwidth_header_subhead">The City That Works</span>
						<div class="et_pb_header_content_wrapper"></div>
						
					</div>
				</div>
					
				</div>
				<div class="et_pb_fullwidth_header_overlay"></div>
				<div class="et_pb_fullwidth_header_scroll"></div>
			</section>
				
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_section --><div class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_1 et_pb_with_background et_section_regular">
				
				
				
				
					<div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_0">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_4_4 et_pb_column_0    et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_0 et_pb_bg_layout_light  et_pb_text_align_left">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner">
					<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="#alltopics">View all topics for &#8220;The City That Works&#8221; &gt;</a></p>
				</div>
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_text --><div class="et_pb_module et_pb_slider et_pb_slider_0 et_pb_slider_fullwidth_off">
				<div class="et_pb_slides">
					<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_0 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center et-pb-active-slide">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">1 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><blockquote>
<p class="p1" style="text-align: left;">One of his top priorities as mayor was to improve the delivery of city services to all of the neighborhoods and to all of the people of Chicago. When you look at the city’s Capital Improvement Program during his administration and the emphasis that was placed on constructing new facilities for every city department, you get a clear picture of the mayor’s priorities. As the City Architect, I had the opportunity and responsibility for the design and construction of these new facilities. New Police, Fire, Health, Senior, Community Service, Library, Streets and Sanitation, and Transit facilities were completed in neighborhoods throughout the city. All designed to improve the delivery of city services.</p>
<p class="p1" style="text-align: right;"><i>Jerome Butler, City Architect, interview excerpt, July 8,2002</i></p>
</blockquote>
<div id="attachment_985" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0067_0002_005.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-985 size-large" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0067_0002_005-1024x827.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley onstage at what is probably a 911 kickoff event. Chicago adopted 911 for all emergency calls in 1976. RJD_04_01_0067_0002_005" width="1024" height="827" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0067_0002_005-1024x827.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0067_0002_005-300x242.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0067_0002_005-1080x873.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0067_0002_005.jpg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Richard J. Daley onstage at what is probably a 911 kickoff event. Chicago adopted 911 for all emergency calls in 1976. RJD_04_01_0067_0002_005</p></div></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_1 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">2 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><p style="text-align: left;">William Daley explains why providing city services was so important for the mayor. Click on image to play video.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">
<!-- iframe plugin v.4.3 wordpress.org/plugins/iframe/ -->
<iframe width="420" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/-5sAOLcvMlc" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" 0="allowfullscreen" scrolling="yes" class="iframe-class"></iframe>
</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Video: William Daley, son of Richard J. Daley, interview excerpt, December 5, 2008</em></p></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_2 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">3 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">I think that you can see how development helps a community. That&#8217;s not only from providing amenities in that area that will serve the people long after it&#8217;s built, but also the jobs it creates to build that amenity.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Patrick Thompson, grandson of Richard J. Daley, interview excerpt, June 13, 2002</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">This undated video shows garbage removal services from the early years of Richard J. Daley&#8217;s mayoral administration. Click on image to play video.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;">
<!-- iframe plugin v.4.3 wordpress.org/plugins/iframe/ -->
<iframe width="420" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/KbqiA2MSlrI" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" 0="allowfullscreen" scrolling="yes" class="iframe-class"></iframe>
<br />
Video: <em>Excerpt from &#8220;Miscellaneous Footage&#8221; (no sound), RJD_04_02_0000_0000_049</em></p></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_3 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">4 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_1740" style="width: 669px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_01_01_0058_0004_020.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-1740 size-large" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_01_01_0058_0004_020-659x1024.jpg" alt="Mayor Richard J. Daley to William L McFetridge of the Chicago Park District, 1967. RJD_01_01_0058_0004_020" width="659" height="1024" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_01_01_0058_0004_020-659x1024.jpg 659w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_01_01_0058_0004_020-193x300.jpg 193w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_01_01_0058_0004_020.jpg 965w" sizes="(max-width: 659px) 100vw, 659px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Mayor Richard J. Daley to William L McFetridge of the Chicago Park District, 1967. RJD_01_01_0058_0004_020</p></div></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_4 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">5 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">Those filtration plants are the lifeblood, not of the city, but of this region. Well, that wasn&#8217;t popular. It wasn&#8217;t popular at all. Build something in the lake? How could you do that? How could you even conceive that? But he knew that was right. He knew that we had to have clean water, if we were going to have cities in the surrounding areas. The foresight that he had was always, &#8220;What&#8217;s good for the city? And what&#8217;s good for its people?&#8221; Politically, at times, it was difficult.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Ed Bedore, City Budget Director, interview excerpt, May 18, 2009</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">Mayor Daley inspects Chicago&#8217;s new water filtration plant. Click on image to play video.</p>

<!-- iframe plugin v.4.3 wordpress.org/plugins/iframe/ -->
<iframe width="420" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/3-j-xihV8-8" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" 0="allowfullscreen" scrolling="yes" class="iframe-class"></iframe>

<p style="text-align: right;"> Video: <em>Excerpt from &#8220;Miscellaneous Footage&#8221; (no sound), RJD_04_02_0000_0000_208</em></p></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_5 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">6 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><p style="text-align: left;">Daley expanded and professionalized police and fire services.</p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">We re-did the headquarters. We built a communications center. We worked with O. W. Wilson in the reorganization of the Police Department and built a series of area headquarters, which were never built before, after Wilson came in. We started with the Area 4 Police Headquarters, then Area 6, and then the Police Training Academy. The city never had a police training academy until Wilson came in. Here’s the fire department. They never had a fire academy until Daley came in. They built a new fire academy.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Jerome Butler, City Architect, interview excerpt, July 8,2002</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">Promotional piece on Chicago&#8217;s police force. Click on image to play video.</p>

<!-- iframe plugin v.4.3 wordpress.org/plugins/iframe/ -->
<iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/NuV9tSpn-Qw" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" 0="allowfullscreen" scrolling="yes" class="iframe-class"></iframe>

<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Video: Excerpts from &#8220;Miscellaneous Footage&#8221; (no sound), RJD_04_02_0000_0000_049</em></p></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_6 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">7 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><div id="attachment_973" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignleft"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0005_001.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-973 size-medium" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0005_001-300x230.jpg" alt="This photo from 1967 shows the snow accumulating at the Wavers Apartment Buildings, at Lamont and Archer. RJD_04_01_0026_0005_001 " width="300" height="230" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0005_001-300x230.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0005_001-1024x784.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0005_001-1080x827.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0026_0005_001.jpg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">This photo from 1967 shows the snow accumulating at the Wavers Apartment Buildings, at Lamont and Archer. RJD_04_01_0026_0005_001</p></div>
<p style="text-align: left;"> In 1967, 23 inches of snow fell within 35 hours &#8212; the largest single snowfall in the city&#8217;s history. Businesses closed, roofs collapsed, cars were abandoned, and many Chicagoans were stranded.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_1947" style="width: 229px" class="wp-caption alignright"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_06_01_0014_0002_001.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-1947 size-medium" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_06_01_0014_0002_001-219x300.jpg" alt="Citation to Richard J. Daley for efforts during 1967 snowstorm from Back of the Yards Neighborhood Council, 1967. RJD_06_01_0014_0002_001" width="219" height="300" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_06_01_0014_0002_001-219x300.jpg 219w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_06_01_0014_0002_001-749x1024.jpg 749w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_06_01_0014_0002_001-1080x1477.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_06_01_0014_0002_001.jpg 1097w" sizes="(max-width: 219px) 100vw, 219px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Citation to Richard J. Daley for efforts during 1967 snowstorm from Back of the Yards Neighborhood Council, 1967. RJD_06_01_0014_0002_001</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">We didn&#8217;t have the power. We didn&#8217;t have the strength. We didn&#8217;t have a good plan. We didn&#8217;t have anything. And Mayor Daley pulled it off because of his charisma on television, telling everyone how good we were doing. We really weren&#8217;t doing so good.</p>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>James McDonough, Commissioner of Department of Streets and Sanitation, interview excerpt, September 17, 2003</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em> </em></p></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_7 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">8 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">The city had a number of programs for youth.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_969" style="width: 835px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0020_0019_011.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-969 size-large" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0020_0019_011-825x1024.jpg" alt="Richard J. Daley pours milk with Scouts on lakefront" width="825" height="1024" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0020_0019_011-825x1024.jpg 825w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0020_0019_011-242x300.jpg 242w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0020_0019_011-1080x1341.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0020_0019_011.jpg 1208w" sizes="(max-width: 825px) 100vw, 825px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Richard J. Daley pours milk with Scouts on lakefront, 1962. RJD_04_01_0020_0019_011</p></div></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_8 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">9 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><div id="attachment_972" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0025_0009_016.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-972 size-large" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0025_0009_016-1024x816.jpg" alt="Youth Foundation award winners at Presidential fitness award event, 1966. RJD_04_01_0025_0009_016" width="1024" height="816" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0025_0009_016-1024x816.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0025_0009_016-300x239.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0025_0009_016-1080x860.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0025_0009_016.jpg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Youth Foundation award winners at Presidential fitness award event, 1966. RJD_04_01_0025_0009_016</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_9 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">10 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Services for the neighborhoods and the wards.</p>
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">I was Alderman of the Ninth Ward from 1971 to 1979—8 years.  The Ninth Ward, under the leadership of Mayor Richard J. Daley, received many important improvements including: a new library in West Pullman, a new grammar school in West Pullman, a new high school in Altgeld-Murray Homes, addition to Curtis Junior High School at 115th Street and State Street, building Chicago Police Department Area 2 Headquarters at 111th and the Calumet Expressway with a City of Chicago Court, City of Chicago Landmark status for Pullman in 1972, and a new roof for Hotel Florence in 1975.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style="text-align: right;"><em>Alexander A. Adduci, Alderman, interview excerpt, July 18, 2014</em></p>
<div id="attachment_953" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/MSLASZ13_0003_0003_002.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-953 size-large" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/MSLASZ13_0003_0003_002-1024x707.jpg" alt="Commissioner of Parks Ed Kelly with Mayor Richard J. Daley at Neighborhood Program event," width="1024" height="707" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/MSLASZ13_0003_0003_002-1024x707.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/MSLASZ13_0003_0003_002-300x207.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/MSLASZ13_0003_0003_002-1080x746.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/MSLASZ13_0003_0003_002.jpg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Commissioner of Parks Ed Kelly with Mayor Richard J. Daley at Neighborhood Program event, ca. 1972-1976. Photo: László Kondor. MSLasz13_0003_0003_002</p></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p></div>
							
						</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide_description -->
					</div>
				</div> <!-- .et_pb_container -->
				
			</div> <!-- .et_pb_slide -->
			<div class="et_pb_slide et_pb_slide_10 et_pb_bg_layout_light et_pb_media_alignment_center">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_container clearfix">
					<div class="et_pb_slider_container_inner">
						
						<div class="et_pb_slide_description">
							<h2 class="et_pb_slide_title">11 of 12</h2>
				<div class="et_pb_slide_content"><div id="attachment_966" style="width: 1034px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><a href="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0018_0004_002.jpg" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="wp-image-966 size-large" src="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0018_0004_002-1024x799.jpg" alt="Civil Defense. Mayor Daley inspects canon drills near Michigan Avenue, 1960. RJD_04_01_0018_0004_002" width="1024" height="799" srcset="https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0018_0004_002-1024x799.jpg 1024w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0018_0004_002-300x234.jpg 300w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0018_0004_002-1080x843.jpg 1080w, https://rjd.library.uic.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2015/05/RJD_04_01_0018_0004_002.jpg 1500w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Civil Defense. Mayor Daley inspects canon drills near Michigan Avenue, 1960. RJD_04_01_0018_0004_002</p></div>
